attrs.content: Ontology Driven Requirements Analysis System: ODRAS captures ontologies and requirements, then estimates a system.
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: The ontology estimation is performed by DAS. By 'guessing' at what ontological instance may be capable of meeting a requirements needs. **This is the core capability of the demonstrator.**
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: The instance table is auto-populated by the estimator but may also be edited and added to by the user.
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: KNowledge Assets are extracted and embedded from documents and requirements, these assets are used by DAS for semantic knowledge.
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: The data manager automatically detects data objects and implements a templated data capture method than can be updated by the user of selected from a set of predefined templates. Update can occur automatically (chron) or by user request.
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: DAS (Digital Assistance System) is semantically aware of project knowledge and project events and can interact with the user input.
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: Captures as a part of standard project activities. The goal is to test and formalize this capability on the WIRR program.
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: Projects are intended to be atomic (small and focused) and hierarchal where main projects are fed information from lower project by import. **The goal is to have an project aware program**
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: Ontologies are a core capability and integration point for the ODRAS system, allowing semantic knowledge capture readable by human and machine.
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: Artifacts are the primary output of the ODRAS tool, typically created by DAS after ontology creation, knowledge capture requirements extraction, and system estimation.
attrs.creator: jdehart
attrs.author: jdehart

attrs.content: We are assuming that ODRAS and the ontology are requirements based. This may or may not be the case.
attrs.creator: jdehart
